<mjml>
  <mj-head>
    <mj-style> h2,img,p { margin:0; } td{ padding-top:0 !important; } p {margin-bottom: 10px;}</mj-style>
    <mj-font name="Roboto" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto" />
    <mj-font name="Roboto+Serif" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto  +Serif:ital,opsz,wght@0,8..144,100..900;1,8..144,100..900&display=swap" />
  </mj-head>
  <mj-body background-color="#f0f1f3"> 
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer> 
    <!-- Logo Header -->  
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff"> 
      <mj-spacer height="10px" />
      <mj-column padding="10px 12px 10px 12px" width="100%">
        <mj-spacer height="16px" />
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" css-class="light_img" width="150px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/gp-logo-grey.png" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" alt="" />
        
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 2px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
            ">Did you know that the King of the UK receives daily updates on government affairs through a red dispatch box every morning?</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
            "><strong>On 15th Jan 2025 edition:</strong> </p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              padding-left: 10px;
            ">→ Verge of hostage-ceasefire deal</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              padding-left: 10px;
            ">→ Baltic sentry</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              padding-left: 10px;
            ">→ Serbia gas challenge</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 0px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-spacer height="10px"></mj-spacer>
    <!-- Spotlight -->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_fsection" background-color="#ffffff" css-class="mj_fsection">
      <mj-column background-color="#ffffff" width="100%">
        <mj-text padding="2px 12px 0px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="white">
          <h2 style="
          padding-top:14px;
          padding-bottom:8px;
          color:#06266D;
            text-align: left;
            letter-spacing:6px;
            border-bottom:2px solid #06266D;
            text-transform:uppercase;
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 300;
              
              
            ">SPOTLIGHT</h2>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section> 
    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">A strategic partnership</h2> 
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-jan-15-1.png" alt="A strategic partnership" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Iran and Russia will sign a partnership agreement at the end of the week to define their relationship and shared strategic interests for the next twenty years. The agreement aims to boost cooperation in trade, investment, transport, logistics, and humanitarian efforts while addressing regional and global issues. It will also solidify their growing military and political partnership. Russia has signed a similar <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-01-2025-h1-1-deal-with-north-korea" target="_blank">deal with North Korea</a>, where they agreed to provide military support in the event of aggression militarily.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4; filter:blur(5px);">Iran and Russia’s relationship has strengthened over the years, particularly since the 2022 war in Ukraine. Iran sent Russia self-detonating <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-01-2025-h1-2-shahed-drones" target="_blank">Shahed drones</a> for its war in Ukraine, but they downplayed its impact and the number of drones sent. Iran also allegedly sent <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-01-2025-h1-3-short-range-ballistic-missiles" target="_blank">short-range ballistic missiles</a>, which they adamantly denied. Russia did little to reciprocate regarding Iran’s proxy wars with Israel and hesitated to send Iran weapons in return.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
  </mj-body>
</mjml>